brewery.brewery_description:
Fiddlehead Brewing Company is located just outside of Burlington, VT in the scenic town of Shelburne. Our owner and Brewmaster Matt “Matty O” Cohen opened the doors on New Year’s Eve of 2011 and since then we have gained worldwide acclaim with our lineup of approachable, multidimensional beers.
  
Our draft, can and bottle offerings are listed on our website.

American Double IPA with tropical fruit notes. Straw colored with a hazy glow. Pineapple and Cantaloupe are dominant characteristics. This beer finishes with a slight tartness.

25% of sales from Mastermind Double IPA are contributed to the Team Mastermind Fund which provides charitable grants to organizations that support pediatric health and broad community wellness.
Porter brewed with house toasted coconut flakes, cacao nibs, vanilla bean and lactose.
Refreshing, Lightly Tart and Hazy Hoppy Pale Ale with Bright Citrus Notes and an Herbal Bitterness.
Citrus, chocolate & burnt sugar notes meld together in this big, hoppy brown ale brewed with brown sugar.
100% Brettanomyces Fermented
Double IPA with wheat and oats.
Traditional wheat ale brewed with coriander, orange peel and our proprietary blend of grains. Hazy and straw colored in appearance. Approachable and satisfying.
Brewed with a pilsner malt base, our American Golden Ale is light and crisp featuring earthy and herbal notes.
Hop forward American style pale ale brewed with oats
Conditioned on Lactose, Vanilla Beans and Hops. This Beer has a creamy mouthfeel and is bursting with Vanilla and Citrus Notes that are reminiscent of a creamsicle.
New England IPA brewed with house yeast blend.
Pale ale brewed with wheat and oats. Aromatics of citrus peel and tropical fruits.
American Double Wheat India Pale Ale
Rustic Saison base, foeder aged with brettanomyces and mixed culture. Notes of lime zest and lemon meringue.
Bright and snappy. Crisp and light. Our fruity and floral pilsner brewed with Noble Hops.
Double IPA brewed exclusively with Columbus Hops. Soft bitterness with a punchy aroma of dank weed and citrus.
Mexican-Style Lager brewed with lime, corn tortillas and agave.
American wild ale with black lava salt, foeder aged with brettanomyces and lactobacillus. Notes of Meyer lemon and custard with a zippy sharp acidity.
Brewed in collaberation with Twiddle, this space age pale ale has notes of passion fruit, pine, and berry fields.
Our Imperial IPA brings the approachability of our beloved Fiddlehead IPA and its signature hoppiness in a stronger format. Bright, citrusy and piney with a well-balanced delivery.
